args: Oof... He's a real deft hand with that\nsword. Practically a genius!
With him as our captain, our order is\nunstoppable. I'd follow him anywhere!
I don't recall commanding you two to talk!\nIdle chatter is what gets soldiers killed.
That's enough sparring for today.\nWe're heading home. Behind me, men!
North Grastaea\nThe Kingdom of Mentzara\nA small, bountiful, and peaceful nation.
The knighthood of Mentzara includes a squad\nof ＂Azure Knights＂ that admits only the most\ntalented of warriors.

The Captain of the Azure Knights is a man
regarded as a hero for the countless victories
he's achieved on the front lines.
His name is Valerio.
Captain Valerio, you've been summoned\nby the king! You need to go to the throne\nroom immediately!
Hm? Very well. I'm on my way.
Yes, Your Majesty.\nHow may I be of service?
I have new orders for you,\neffective immediately.
I'm assigning you to guard detail\nfor my daughter, Primia.
As the captain of the Azure Knights,\nI know that she will be safe in your care.\nDo not disappoint me, Valerio.
(I'm the finest blade in the kingdom,\nand he wants me guarding his child?!)
Your Majesty, if I may be so bold,\nI could suggest some candidates who\nwould be more fit for this duty than I.
I believe my talents are best suited for\nthe battlefield. And more importantly,\nchildren are not my forte.
Then this will be a fine opportunity for\nyou. Furthermore, the princess herself—
That's right! I requested you myself!
Hee hee. I'm so looking forward to this,\nValerio!
And so began Valerio's new life as the\nPrincess's royal knight. Until one day...
Do try to keep up, Valerio!

Your Highness, you must cease these
strolls through town! Might I suggest
you return to the castle to read,
or perhaps—
Blech, no way! Now hurry up, or I'm\nleaving you behind.
(I knew this assignment would be\na poor fit. I'm hopeless when it\ncomes to dealing with children!)

(I was born to serve on the battlefield.
Yet with a word, she was able to make
me her royal knight. Perhaps with another,
she can return me to my order...)
Ever in your wake, Your Highness.
(How does she know her way around\nthese back alleys so well? What does\nshe seek in a place like this?)
Ah, there you are!\nGather round, friends!
Your Highness, what are you doing?!
Here are those cookies, as promised!

That's right. While we were walking
through town several days ago, I spoke
with these children, who mentioned they'd
never once had cookies. Can you imagine?
Thus did I promise that when next we met,\nI would bring them some. Did I not?
You sure did, Your Highness! Just look\nat them all... There's gotta be five days'\nworth! We'll savor every last bite.
Oh, splendid! I'll be sure to bring even\nmore next time, then. That's a promise!
YOU WILL?! Thank you sooooooo much!
You dragged me along on this walk\njust so you could deliver some cookies?
I did. Am I sorry? Only a little.
Now tell me, Valerio:\nHow do you eat cookies?
Er... The same as the next person.\nI have a few when I want a light snack,\nperhaps paired with tea.
I do the same.\nBut for those kids, it's different.

I eat that many cookies in a day,
but they plan to make them last for five.
And when they eat them, I'm sure they'll
appreciate them more than I ever have.
As their princess, it is my duty to keep\nthem all fed and happy.
To this end, I intend to grow ever stronger.\nLike you, Valerio.
Just so. You are a hero of this nation!\nAnd when I grow up, I want to do\nmy part to protect it too.
So until that day comes... I beseech you,\nprotect this country with me. Please!
(I've only been seeing her as a child.\nWhy haven't I ever noticed?)

(Her petite frame bears the weight of great
responsibility. As an adult, it is my duty
to help her bear that burden. Yet I have
been thinking only of myself.)
(Maybe the best way to protect\nmy country...is by protecting her.)
I understand, Your Highness.\nI vow to keep you safe.\nI stake my life upon it.
Hee hee! I knew you wouldn't\nlet me down, Valerio.
Thus did Valerio spend many peaceful days\nas the royal knight of Princess Primia.
Valerio was touched by the purity of Primia's\nvision for her country, and gradually found\nhimself yearning to make her dreams come true.

But contrary to Primia and Valerio's wishes,
conditions in Mentzara were deteriorating.
Worse still, a neighboring nation had begun
to openly provoke conflict.
Suddenly, the flames of war began to kindle...
